The paper discusses the formal security analysis of neural networks, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of Satisfiability Modulo Theory (SMT) solvers also suggests the possibility of the paper belonging to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) category. The deployment of DNNs in security-critical domains also indicates the relevance of the paper to the systems and control (cs.SY) category. Finally, the paper presents a new approach for formally checking security properties, which could be of interest to the software engineering (cs.SE) community.
